Ask HN: You want to build new Twitter. Your Architecture/Tech stack?
text:
Hey Architects and Engineers! Lend me your ears!

Let's say you have your savings. And you want to build a new Twitter with pretty much the same feature set.

Where would you do that and how? What your tech stack would look like? Postgres, RabbitMQ, Kafka, Redis, OpenSearch, Cockroach DB etc and what piece would do what?

Where would you host it intially and eventually? AWS? GCP? Azure? Hetzner?

How much time to the MVP? Backend in Golang/Python or something else? Frontend React/Sevelte or what?

I'm looking for a complete comprehensive plan that is practical. Think of it as something you want to showcase as your pragmatic rational technical excellence.

With these words, I leave the stage to you.

Ask HN: Review my dev portfolio startup
text:
Hey, Felix from Stage here

Over the last couple of months we talked to engineers at the biggest tech companies like Google, Uber, Zillow & so many more to gain a good understanding how to approach the portfolio & dev reputation game.

The developer portfolio is a major part in presenting yourself as an developer. So we thought there could be an opportunity to improve this type of work & make it less painful, automate more & provide high value, so, today I'm proud to present you:

https://getstage.app

Stage is an API based developer portfolio, bring your data from sources like GitHub, LinkedIn, Spotify & more, ootb gorgeous design & be always in-sync. You can even create custom extensions w/ code.

With the layoffs crushing our industry atm, it's the first time in like a decade where it's even more important to have a good presentation online if you're affected. With our approach of fetching data from other sources, you don't go to update-hell. Just keep on updating the platforms & services you are anyway using.

What will it cost you ask? Creating a portfolio will be free, forever. We currently thinking about adding an paid analytics layer on top of it & also 1 really interested feature which was highly requested –> Tailoring: Fork your portfolio for a specific job or audience. Highlight / Hide different things based on one specific job description for example.

But there is so much more!! We're really excited to ship an alpha version by the end of the year and would be so happy if you share what you think :)
